Package model.wheel

Interface Slot

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SlotImpl
    public interface Slot
    Represents a slot in the Further Programming Assignment

    This interface should be implemented as SlotImpl

    Note: Slot positions increment clockwise around the wheel, whereas slot numbers follow the order as defined in Wheel.SLOT_NUMBERS

    Author:
    Ross Nye
    See Also:
    SlotImpl, Wheel

      • toString

        java.lang.String toString()
        Override Object.toString(). Generates a string representing the slot as seen in the output trace. The following are examples of such strings.
        • Slot position=01, color=Double Zero, number=00
        • Slot position=20, color=Green Zero, number=0
        • Slot position=21, color=Black, number=28
        • Slot position=22, color=Red, number=9
        Note: You may find it useful to also override and use SlotColor.toString() to produce these results.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        a string representing the slot as seen in the output trace
